{{Quote|This is a dangerous situation, Your Highness. Our security volunteers will be no match against a battle-hardened Federation army.|Quarsh Panaka, to Queen Amidala|<ref name="Episode I" />}}
The '''Royal Naboo Security Forces'''<ref name="USWNE">''[[Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition]]''</ref> ('''RNSF'''),<ref name="HC 54">{{HelmetCollectionCite|13|Helmets}}</ref> also known as the '''Naboo Royal Guards''', the '''Naboo Royal Security Forces''',<ref name="DB">{{Databank|naboo-royal-guards|Naboo Royal Guards}}</ref> the '''Royal Security Forces'''<ref name="SWCT Pilot">{{SWCT|set=Base Series 1|cardname=Naboo Pilot - Galactic Republic}}</ref> or the '''Volunteer Security Forces'''<ref name="Altay">{{EncyclopediaCite|Naboo}}</ref> were the [[corps]] responsible for [[Law enforcement agency|policing]] the [[planet]] of [[Naboo]] as well as protecting its [[Monarch of Naboo|monarch]] and [[Naboo (people)|people]].<ref name="NRSF" />

The Security Forces, while mostly composed of volunteers, were trained in [[Unarmed combat|hand-to-hand combat]] and marksmanship, as well as responding to attacks such as [[assassin]]ation attempts against the Naboo [[Monarchy|monarch]]. However, the Security Forces were a policing organization, and not trained as a standing army. The Security Forces included three divisions: the [[Naboo Palace Guard]], the [[Security Guard]], and the [[Naboo Royal Space Fighter Corps]].<ref name="NRSF" />

During the [[Invasion of Naboo]] the Security Forces, under the command of [[Captain]] [[Quarsh Panaka|Panaka]], were overwhelmed by the [[Trade Federation]]'s [[Trade Federation Droid Army|droid army]]. With the assistance of the [[Jedi]] they were able to evacuate [[Queen]] [[Padmé Amidala]] on her [[Naboo Royal Starship]] [[pilot]]ed by veteran Fighter Corps member, [[Ric Olié]]. Later, during the [[Battle of Naboo]], the Security Forces retook their [[homeworld]] with the assistance of the Jedi and the native [[Gungan]]s.<ref name="Episode I" /> Overall, the Security Forces grew during Amidala's rule of Naboo; whilst Amidala was largely a pacifist, she understood the need for security, and Panaka was obsessed with keeping the planet and monarch safe, especially after the invasion.<ref name="Queen's Shadow" />

When Amidala became a [[Senator]], she continued to receive protection from a Security Forces detail under the command of Captain [[Gregar Typho]]. During Amidala's return to [[Coruscant]], Typho was able to disguise her using a [[Cordé|decoy]]. His concerns were well founded, as the [[J-type diplomatic barge|shuttle]] came under [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala|attack]], [[Death|killing]] several guards, though Amidala survived.<ref name="Episode II" />

Several members of the Forces gave their lives assisting Jedi Master [[Kelleran Beq]] in his rescue of [[Din Grogu|Grogu]] during [[Operation: Knightfall]].<ref name="Chapter 20">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 20: The Foundling}}</ref>

==History==
The security forces under Captain [[Quarsh Panaka]] served under Queen [[Sanandrassa]] until the election of [[Padmé Amidala]].<ref name="Queen's Peril">''[[Queen's Peril]]''</ref> During the Trade Federation's [[Invasion of Naboo|Blockade]], the security forces were no match for the [[Trade Federation Droid Army]]. However, Panaka and his detachment were able to escape Naboo with Amidala and Jedi Master [[Qui-Gon Jinn]] to [[Tatooine]] and eventually [[Coruscant]]. The remaining security forces stayed behind and formed a [[Naboo Resistance|resistance]] force. Upon Amidala's return to Naboo, the Security forces, with the Gungans distracting the main droid army, were able to help Amidala capture Viceroy [[Nute Gunray]]. The security forces later took part in a parade to celebrate both Naboo's and the Gungan's victory over the Trade Federation.<ref name="Episode I" />

